<center><h1> CSS </h1></center>
<h1 style="font-size: 18px;  border:2px solid #333; 
          padding:10px; 
          background-color:lightblue; 
          border-radius:8px; 
          display:inline-block;">ICSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is a stylesheet language used to describe the presentation of a document written in HTML or XML. It controls how elements appear on a webpage, such as layout, colors, fonts, spacing, and responsiveness. CSS allows developers to separate content from design, making websites easier to maintain and more consistent in appearance.</h1>
          <ul>There are three main types of CSS based on how the styles are applied to HTML:

<ol>
<li>Inline CSS is used directly within an HTML element using the style attribute. It affects only that specific element.</li>

<li>Internal CSS is written inside a style tag within the <head> section of an HTML document.</li>

<li>Inline CSS is used directly within an HTML element using the style attribute.</li>
    </ol>
    </ul>
    
  <h1 class="table">Basic CSS Properties</h1>

  <table border="1">
    <tr>
      <th>Property</th>
      <th>Description</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>color</td>
      <td>Sets the text color</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>background-color</td>
      <td>Sets the background color</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>font-size</td>
      <td>Sets the size of the text</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>text-align</td>
      <td>Aligns text (left, center, right)</td>
    </tr>
  
  </table>
